      "content": "Your doubt that a standard medical address or a hollow vessel do no good is a valid feeling when the person *experiencing* the emptiness. It is understandable to feel like the alternative to that void is to keep holding the door of a cold room. Please remember that while you may feel like a shell, observing this from the outside might paradoxically help you discover what's needed. It is often necessary to find a person who will listen without judgment or push back, rather than just repeating advice. Please consider continuing to reach out to your support system or a professional; it can be very difficult without one, even feeling the need to do something about it.",
